  "text": "Over the years, Lagrangian numerical models have developed complex representations of the relevant processes: starting from two-dimensional point source particle-tracking models such as TESEO-PICHI [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , we arrive at complex oil slick polygon representations and three-dimensional advection-diffusion models [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . At the time being, state-of-the-art published Lagrangian oil spill models do not include the possibility to model threedimensional physical-chemical transformation processes.",
